ctions to manage difficult  ...     MISO took 84 percent fewer manual re-dispatch actions than last winter;  ...    • Roughly half of the $32 million FTR shortfall was caused by a late-reported  ...    succession. MISO effectively managed the system with no emergencies.  A polar vortex produced record low temperatures in most of Midwest, including  ...    • MISO managed the system reliably, applying lessons learned from prior storms  ...     On net, virtual demand lost $31 million, compared to profits of $28 million and  ...    Highlights for Winter 2024\n© 2024 Potomac Economics -10-\nDemand Response Participation in MISO • FERC has agreed to settlements totaling more than $100 million with Demand Response Resources (DRR) that we referred to FERC for market manipulation.  The latest DRR agreed to a settlement of more than $66 million in January, of  ...     We have been working with MISO on tariff changes to reduce its exposure to  ...    • NERC recently issued a report finding serious reliability concerns in MISO.  ...    • MISO is soon taking a critical step by filing a proposal to accredit capacity  ...     Together with proposed projects in the queue, new gas resources total more  ...     These initiatives, together with proposed storage and hybrid resources, are  ...     We remain concerned that reliance on increasingly unrealistic Future 2A (and  ...    © 2024 Potomac Economics -12-\nDuring the Winter Quarter, we:  ...    • Presented the IMM Fall Quarterly report to the MSC and recent market results \nto the ERSC.  ...    • Continued working with MISO to review proposals to revise the M2M “firm  ...    © 2024 Potomac Economics -13-\nDay-Ahead Average Monthly Hub Prices\nWinter 2022–2024\n© 2024 Potomac Economics -14- All-In Price\nWinter 2022 – 2024\n© 2024 Potomac Economics -15-\nAncillary Services Prices\nWinter 2023–2024\n-$9\n-$6\n-$3\n$0  ...    D J F M A M J J A S O N D J F D J F M A M J J A S O N D J F D J F M A M J J A S O N D J F D J F M A M 